# Corporate Ladder — Project Context

Telegram Mini App: climb the corporate ladder, avoid meetings/reorgs/deadlines. "Lumberjack meets modern office life."

## Stack

- Frontend: `apps/mini-app` (TypeScript, Vite, Tailwind) → Vercel
- API: `packages/api` (FastAPI) → Railway
- Bot: `apps/bot` (aiogram) → Railway
- DB: Supabase Postgres (`supabase/migrations/`)

## MVP v1 Scope

**Shipped:** core gameplay, Telegram auth, Daily + Weekly leaderboards, share, bot launch. v1.5 design polish, v1.6 fairness/onboarding, and v1.7 daily shift complete in code.

**Out:** Friends leaderboard (v1.1), All-time tab (v1.1), currency, skins, clans, quests, NFTs.

**Next release train:** v1.7 tag/deploy gate → v1.8 narrative beats + arena identity — see [ROADMAP.md](../../ROADMAP.md). Match ROADMAP § Shipped baseline for v1.6+ mechanics.

## Principles

1. **Humor is the product** — preserve satirical tone in all copy.
2. **No secrets in frontend** — bot token and Supabase service key stay on Railway only.
3. **Minimal scope** — do not add v1.1 features without explicit approval.
4. **Match prototype** — [`snippet.txt`](../../snippet.txt) is mechanics canon; port, don't reinvent (parity notes at file footer).
5. **Terminology** — UI uses Energy / Deadline; code obstacle type `burnout` unchanged.

## Family

Sibling repo: [DITreneris/site](https://github.com/DITreneris/site) (Prompt Anatomy marketing). Shared doc/changelog/verifier habits; this repo keeps satirical Telegram game scope.

